# Deployment Utils for mos-erver

## Copy website files to server
scp -r /Users/matteoosio/Documents/mos-erver/website/* mos@192.168.0.100:/home/mos/mos-erver/

## Restart service (only if needed - static files usually don't require restart)
ssh mos@192.168.0.100 "sudo systemctl restart mos-erver.service"

## Check service status
ssh mos@192.168.0.100 "sudo systemctl status mos-erver.service"

## View service logs
ssh mos@192.168.0.100 "sudo journalctl -u mos-erver.service -f"

## One-liner: Deploy and restart
scp -r /Users/matteoosio/Documents/mos-erver/website/* mos@192.168.0.100:/home/mos/mos-erver/ && ssh mos@192.168.0.100 "sudo systemctl restart mos-erver.service"